# Exclusions for `npm pack` from paths NOT covered by `package.json#files`.
#
# `package.json#files` is the include allowlist. Per npm's documented
# precedence, paths inside `files`-listed directories CANNOT be excluded by a
# top-level `.npmignore`, so this file is not the right tool for filtering
# specific files out of `docs/`, `scripts/`, etc.
#
# The canonical defenses are:
# - `npm run build:release-archive` (T-V05-013) stages a transformed copy under
#   `.release-staging/` with numbered ADRs filtered and shipping `docs/**/*.md`
#   replaced by the stub form. The release workflow packs that staged tree.
# - `scripts/release-prepack-guard.mjs` (wired as the `prepack` lifecycle
#   script) refuses `npm pack` of `@luis85/agentic-workflow` from any cwd that
#   lacks the `.release-staging-marker`, so a maintainer who bypasses the
#   build script and runs bare `npm pack` from the repo root fails closed.
#
# The exclusions below cover paths that are NOT in `package.json#files` and
# therefore would only appear in the tarball if the `files` field were widened
# by accident — pure belt-and-braces.
#
# When changing this file, also update:
# - `package.json#files` (the canonical include list).
# - `scripts/lib/release-archive-builder.ts` (build-time filter).
# - `scripts/release-prepack-guard.mjs` (prepack guard).
# - `docs/release-package-contents.md` (the contract documentation).
# - `tools/automation-registry.yml` (the automation inventory).

# Local maintainer state — never relevant to consumers.
.worktrees/

# Build-time staging directory produced by `npm run build:release-archive`.
# Excluded so that staging output cannot recursively land inside a packed
# archive when the release pipeline is rerun against a dirty checkout.
.release-staging/
